, 66.75], [-72.5, 66.5], [-73, 66.5]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [{"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "http://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/canimage/50k/036/i/canimage_036i10_tif.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "ftp://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/canimage/50k/036/i/canimage_036i10_tif.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}], "browse_graphic_url": "http://www.fakeimageurl123.com/foo.jpg", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "2001-07-27", "data_series_name": "CanImage - Ortho-images Landsat 7 du Canada, 1/50 000", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "2001-07-27", "notes": "CanImage is a raster image containing information from Landsat 7 orthoimages that have been resampled and based on the National Topographic System (NTS) at the 1:50 000 scale in the UTM projection. The product is distributed in files in GeoTIFF format. The resolution of this product is 15 metres. The Landsat 7 ortho images contain 8 spectral bands. For the creation of the CanImage product, the following bands were retained: band 3 (red), 2 (green) and 1 (green-blue). These bands are displayed using the colors: red (band 3), green (band 2) and blue (band 1). A linear stretching is done on each of the 3 band in order to increase the contrast. The clipping of the product according to the NTS in the UTM projection generate an overlap between the adjacent CanImage data sets.", "title": "